summary: This document is a search and seizure warrant issued by the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York. It authorizes law enforcement to search electronic devices seized from Little Saint James in the Virgin Islands, related to violations of sex trafficking laws involving minors and conspiracy. The warrant outlines the devices to be searched and the evidence sought.

events.title: Search of Little Saint James
events.description: Law enforcement executed a search warrant on Little Saint James, recovering multiple electronic devices.

keyFacts: The search warrant was issued for electronic devices seized from Little Saint James on August 12, 2019.
The warrant is related to violations of 18 USC 1591 (Sex Trafficking of Minors) and 18 USC 371 (Sex Trafficking Conspiracy).
The document lists various electronic devices, including multiple Mac computers, laptops, and servers, to be searched for evidence of sex trafficking.
The warrant allows for the review of electronic stored information (ESI) for evidence related to the identity of users and communications with co-conspirators.
The warrant includes provisions for delayed notice to the person whose property is being searched.
